SIMPLE: albacore
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Albacore
<hw>Al"ba*core</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A name applied to several large fishes of the Mackerel family
(<fam>Scombridae</fam>), esp. <spn>Thunnus alalunga</spn> (formerly
<spn>Orcynus alalonga</spn>); it is a type of <isa>tuna</isa> or
<isa>tunny</isa>. The name has been also applied to a larger related
species, <spn>Thunnus thynnus</spn> (formerly <spn>Orcynus
thynnus</spn>), common in the <geog>Mediterranean</geog> and
<geog>Atlantic</geog>, which is called in <geog>New England</geog> the
<altname>horse mackerel</altname>.</def> <altsp>[formerly spelled
<asp>albicore</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Alban</ent>⟦br⟧
